@Larry Berger

Why would seeing someone else share their impression of a puzzle affect your enjoyment of it? 

That makes no sense to me.  We're in many places with regards to experience, tenacity, knowledge and many other factors, so it seems natural that we would see things differently.

@Asher

There's a puzzle I struggle with every week.  With rare exceptions, on the few (very few) days I can actually complete it one sitting, I know that the person reviewing will say it was particularly easy.  Different person, different experience.  I'm stilled thrilled with my accomplishment.

When people say the puzzle is "too easy", for the most part they're not bragging, but expressing disappointment that the challenge they expect on a weekend puzzle was not there.  Try looking at the comments from that perspective.

@Jerry
